Ordered from this place for the first time on UberEats for delivery and boy, was this a disappointment. Two friends and myself were craving some delicious Italian food, so we wanted to get the family pasta dinner deal. Which sounded great for three people, considering you get a choice of one app, one pasta, and one salad for $40. The restaurant explains that it’s designed to feed 3-4 people. When our food arrived, we found a measly 5 raviolis, 5 spinach/feta triangles, and the worst little caprese salad I’ve ever seen (it was a few slices of tomato and mozz on top of a bunch of wilted spring mix - which is not even how caprese should be prepared). The ravioli tasted like it was frozen and heated up. Oh yeah, and the “family meal” came with one very small breadstick. What a scam. This meal is barely enough to feed two people. Save your money and go somewhere else.

Came here last night/earlier this morning (Sunday, 4/17) around 3am with a friend to get some slices of pizza. After I placed my order, I stepped aside to wait for my pizza to be ready. While waiting, a belligerent guy in line to order pizza assaulted another guy standing behind him in line. No one expelled the guy from the pizzeria. Within minutes of that first assault, the friend that I was with who was standing in front of me, was assaulted by that same belligerent guy. He punched my friend in the mouth and knocked him to the floor. He then tried to go after him again while he was down and I was trying to help him up, that guy knocked my glasses off of my face and broke them. When I got my broken glasses back on, I didn't see the guy again. No one in the pizzeria, neither the staff nor patrons, were at all concerned about the two assaults that had just occurred. I didn't expect patrons to intervene, but I was greatly disappointed and upset that no one working there came over to us to ask us how we were or if we wanted them to call the police. Instead, they just ignored us and didn't do anything. That is terrible business and customer service. I will never go to this place again. I feel unsafe there now and know that I can't rely on the staff to do anything about that because they seem not to care.

IKU doesn't really serve your typical DC jumbo slice - these are big, but not of the gargantuan proportions you get at a place like Duccini's.  What is does serve is good late night pizza, 6 nights a week (they close earlier on Sundays), as well as having a full menu of Italian food during regular business and dinner hours.  The staff is friendly, the service is quick, and it's not too expensive.
